\sum_{i, j} S(i, j) = X
\sum_j S(i,j) = C_i
\sum_i S(i,j) = R_j
\implies \sum_{i, j} C_i S(i, j) \ge \sum_{i, j} R_j S(i, j) 
\implies \sum_{i} C_i C_i \ge \sum_{j} R_j R_j 
\implies \sum_{i=1}^n C_i^2 \ge \sum_{j=1}^m R_j^2 
